      "before_mean": 28.21,
      "after_mean": 64.63
    },
    "ngrams": {
      "window": [
        2000,
        2022
      ],
      "n_years": 23,
      "crossover_year_50pct": null,
      "changepoint_year": 2014,
      "K_stat": 120,
      "p_value": 0.002216,
      "significant_at_0.05": true,
      "before_mean": 18.91,
      "after_mean": 33.98
    },
    "interpretation": "Two complementary tests on the Kiev/Kyiv yearly adoption (2000\u2013). (1) Pettitt's non-parametric changepoint test finds a statistically significant regime shift in both sources: Open Library titles in 2017 (p = 0.007056, mean 28.21% \u2192 64.63%) and Google Ngrams body text in 2014 (p = 0.002216, mean 18.91% \u2192 33.98%). (2) The 50% crossover year \u2014 when the Ukrainian form first overtakes the Russian one \u2014 is 2019 for Open Library titles and never reached in window for Google Ngrams body text. The crossover-year gap is the publisher-vs-author lag: titles (publisher decisions) flip earlier than the body text (citing older sources)."
  },
